  "root_text": {
    "sn4.9:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 4.9 ",
    "sn4.9:0.2": "1. Paṭhamavagga ",
    "sn4.9:0.3": "Paṭhamaāyusutta ",
    "sn4.9:1.1": "Evaṁ me sutaṁ—",
    "sn4.9:1.2": "ekaṁ samayaṁ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. ",
    "sn4.9:1.3": "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
    "sn4.9:1.4": "“bhikkhavo”ti. ",
    "sn4.9:1.5": "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṁ. ",
    "sn4.9:1.6": "Bhagavā etadavoca: ",
    "sn4.9:2.1": "“Appamidaṁ, bhikkhave, manussānaṁ āyu. ",
    "sn4.9:2.2": "Gamanīyo samparāyo, kattabbaṁ kusalaṁ, caritabbaṁ brahmacariyaṁ. ",
    "sn4.9:2.3": "Natthi jātassa amaraṇaṁ. ",
    "sn4.9:2.4": "Yo, bhikkhave, ciraṁ jīvati, so vassasataṁ appaṁ vā bhiyyo”ti. ",
    "sn4.9:3.1": "Atha kho māro pāpimā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṁ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ",
    "sn4.9:4.1": "“Dīghamāyu manussānaṁ, ",
    "sn4.9:4.2": "na naṁ hīḷe suporiso; ",
    "sn4.9:4.3": "Careyya khīramattova, ",
    "sn4.9:4.4": "natthi maccussa āgamo”ti. ",
    "sn4.9:5.1": "“Appamāyu manussānaṁ, ",
    "sn4.9:5.2": "hīḷeyya naṁ suporiso; ",
    "sn4.9:5.3": "Careyyādittasīsova, ",
    "sn4.9:5.4": "natthi maccussa nāgamo”ti. ",
    "sn4.9:6.1": "Atha kho māro …pe… tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn4.9:0.1": "Linked Discourses 4.9 ",
    "sn4.9:0.2": "1. Lifespan ",
    "sn4.9:0.3": "Lifespan (1st) ",
    "sn4.9:1.1": "So I have heard. ",
    "sn4.9:1.2": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. ",
    "sn4.9:1.3": "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, ",
    "sn4.9:1.4": "“Mendicants!” ",
    "sn4.9:1.5": "“Venerable sir,” they replied. ",
    "sn4.9:1.6": "The Buddha said this: ",
    "sn4.9:2.1": "“Mendicants, the lifespan of humans is short. ",
    "sn4.9:2.2": "You must go to the next life. So you should do what is skillful, you should practice the spiritual life. ",
    "sn4.9:2.3": "No-one born is immortal. ",
    "sn4.9:2.4": "A long life is a hundred years or a little more.” ",
    "sn4.9:3.1": "Then Māra the Wicked went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse: ",
    "sn4.9:4.1": "“The life of humans is long! ",
    "sn4.9:4.2": "A true person wouldn’t scorn it. ",
    "sn4.9:4.3": "Live like a suckling babe, ",
    "sn4.9:4.4": "for Death has not come for you.” ",
    "sn4.9:5.1": "“The life of humans is short, ",
    "sn4.9:5.2": "and a true person scorns it. ",
    "sn4.9:5.3": "They should live as though their head was on fire, ",
    "sn4.9:5.4": "for Death comes for everyone.” ",
    "sn4.9:6.1": "Then Māra … vanished right there. "
  },
